						dextr&egrave;.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Skillfully.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						distinctio urbana.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				An urbane distinction.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						argut&egrave;.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Cleverly.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="90">
					<marginalia_text>
						Statim discitur, aut fit, cum Hoc agitur. Proprium quarto modo.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				One immediately learns, or becomes, when This is done. Proper to the fourth way.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
	
